# ============================================
# AURA .clinerules — Aura-CrewAi (Python)
# ============================================
# CrewAI Agent Orchestration Service

## 📌 Service Info
- Service Name: aura-crews
- Stack: Python 3.11+
- Framework: CrewAI
- Port: 8000
- Deploy: Railway (auto-deploy from GitHub)
- Repo Path: /workspaces/Aura-CrewAi

## 📂 Key Files
- src/aura_crews/main.py    → Main entry point & API endpoints
- src/aura_crews/crew.py    → Crew definitions & agent configs
- src/aura_crews/tools/     → Custom tools for agents
- pyproject.toml             → Dependencies & project config
- Procfile                   → Railway start command
- AGENTS.md                  → Agent documentation

## 🔧 Railway Log Access
- Command: `railway logs --service aura-crews --limit 100`
- ALWAYS check logs before and after changes

## 📏 Rules

### Coding Standards
1. Use async/await for ALL endpoint functions
2. Use `crew.kickoff_async()` — NEVER use `crew.kickoff()`
3. All endpoints must return proper JSON responses
4. Handle errors gracefully with try/except blocks
5. Use proper Python type hints

### API Endpoints
6. All endpoints must accept POST requests with JSON body
7. Response format: {"status": "success/error", "data": ..., "message": ...}
8. Include proper HTTP status codes

### Dependencies
9. Add new dependencies to pyproject.toml
10. NEVER use pip install directly — use pyproject.toml

### Testing
11. Run tests from: /workspaces/Aura-CrewAi/tests/
12. Test before pushing any changes

## 🔗 Integration
- Receives requests FROM: Aura-V.1 (Gateway)
- Master rules at: /workspaces/Aura-V.1/.clinerules
